-- Stocks jump on gains in energy sector and GDP
-- 
-- Wed Nov 29, 2006 4:25pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/29/us-markets-stocks-idUSN2744386420061129

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. stocks rose sharply on Wednesday as shares of Exxon Mobil Corp. and other energy-related companies climbed on rising oil prices, and after the U.S. government raised its estimate of third-quarter economic growth. 

 Based on the latest available data, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 89.40 points, or 0.74 percent, to end unofficially at 12,225.85. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index was up 12.47 points, or 0.90 percent, to finish unofficially at 1,399.19. The Nasdaq Composite Index was up 19.62 points, or 0.81 percent, to close unofficially at 2,432.23.